Hello!
This is a Telegram bot repository with a simple interface, but with an interesting backend implementation that displays information about the sights of the entered city by name.
Technologies used: Java 15, SpringBoot, SpringMVC, SpringData, PostgreSQL, Hibernate, Maven, GIT.
The bot implements REST WebService.
While there are several cities in the database:
«Минск», «Москва», «Варшава», «Киев», «Рига», «Пекин», «Вильнюс» .
The bot is configured to run it either on a local server or on a remote server.
The bot is deployed for hosting Heroku (free tariff), so to wake up the bot, you need to send a GET request in the browser "https://touristtestbot.herokuapp.com/api/cities"
Bot nickname: @BestTouristBot
Bot token: 1529852801: AAELj5FDxkz65oHZ4c8OcvY72G5COJ5uohc

Required to run (remote server):
- telegram account
- find a bot by nickname "@BestTouristBot"
- send a GET request in the browser to wake up the bot "https://touristtestbot.herokuapp.com/api/cities"
-start testing by entering cities with a capital letter in Russian, for example «Москва».

Required to run (local server):
- telegram account
- find a bot by nickname "@BestTouristBot"
- import bot repository from github
- pull up pomfile dependencies
- run the application class
